getValues

public java.lang.Integer[] getValues()
Returns an Integer array of the values. CH1 is located in the first element of the array, CH2 in the second one, and so on. If CHi is not active for this feature, the (i-1)th element is null.

Returns:
all the values as an array of Integer

compareTo

public int compareTo(java.lang.Object o)
Compares this Feature to another Object. If the Object is a Feature, this function compares hierarchically (and in the following order) the physical id, the sensorCode, the featureCode and the channelBitmask. Otherwise, it throws a ClassCastException (as Strings are comparable only to other Strings).

Specified by:
compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable
Parameters:
o - the Object to be compared.
Returns:
the value 0 if the argument is a Feature is "equal" to this Feature; -1 if this Feature "precede" the argument o; +1 otherwise.
